verses.text:
Ask and it will be given to you;
seek and you shall find;
knock and it will be opened to you.

The Lord is my Shepherd
I am not lacking in anything;
He lays me down in grassy pastures.

Taste and see
how good the Lord is;
blessed is the man who trusts in Him.

God's mercy has not ended,
and His mercy was not exhausted. It is updated every morning;
Your faithfulness is great!

And Jesus had mercy,
touched their eyes;
and now they have opened their eyes...

don't be afraid
for I am with you;
do not perish, for I am your God; I will strengthen you and help you

If your sins be as scarlet,
- white as snow;
if they are red like purple, I will whiten them like wool

I told you this
that you may have peace in Me. In the world you will have sorrow;
but take courage: I have overcome the world

And whom He appointed
called them;
and whom he called, those he justified; and whom he justified, those he glorified

And I will contemplate Your face in truth;
waking up
I will be satisfied with Your image

So,
let us approach the throne of grace with courage,
to accept mercy and find grace for timely help

Do not get carried away by all kinds of other people's sciences,
for it is good grace to strengthen hearts,
and not with dishes that were of no use to those who followed them

From there they sailed to Antioch,
from where the grace of God was entrusted to work,
which they did

Call upon Me in the day of trouble;
i will set you free
and you will glorify Me.

He restores my soul;
leads me along the paths of truth
for the sake of His name.

Whoever desires, let him come;
and who wants
let life take water stupidly.

Do not rejoice over me, my enemy:
when I fall, I will stand up;
when I sit in the dark - the Lord is my light!

the Lord is with me
like a mighty knight;
therefore my persecutors will stumble.

A new song — to the Lord,
for He has done strange things;
His right hand overcame and His holy arm.

By Your power You gave me
the power of the bull;
You anointed me with fresh oil.

When you cross the waters - I am with you,
and through the rivers - they will not flood you;
when you walk through the fire, you won't get burned.

By faith Abraham obeyed as he was called,
to go to the place he was supposed to inherit;
and went out, not knowing where he was going.

For by faith you have been saved by grace,
and this is not from you - it is a gift from God;
not of works, so that no one may boast.

Ask and it will be given to you;
seek and you will find;
knock and it will be opened to you.

And there is no salvation in any other;
for there is no other name under heaven
given to the people we need to be saved.

But let him ask with faith,
without doubting anything;
for he who doubts is like a wave of the sea.

Whom you love without seeing;
in whom you believe, although you do not see now,
and rejoice with unspeakable and glorious joy.

Jesus said to her:
I am the resurrection and the life;
whoever believes in Me, even though he dies, he will live.

I will lie down and fall asleep;
i wake up
for the Lord supports me.

I lie down and sleep in peace
for You alone, Lord,
you let me live safely

But I calmed and soothed my soul,
like a child separated from its mother;
like a weaned child, so is my soul.

I do not reject the grace of God,
for when righteousness is through the law,
then Christ died in vain!

The Lord is my rock,
my fortress and my deliverer;
My God is my rock, I take refuge in Him...

Fear not, for I am with you;
do not be afraid, for I am your God:
I will strengthen you and help you.

the Lord your God
This one will go before you;
He will destroy these nations before you.

They surrounded me like bees,
they were extinguished like the fire of thorns;
in the name of the Lord I will cut them off!

You are my hiding place;
You will save me from oppression
and surround me with songs of deliverance.

And without faith it is impossible to please God;
for whoever comes to God
must believe that He is.

And said to her:
Donya, your faith saved you;
go in peace

I will lie down peacefully and fall asleep,
for only You, Lord,
you let me live safely

Put your burden on the Lord,
and He will support you;
He will never shake the righteous.
